{"author":{"id":"aed0d72ca16b13a779b1d37a0771f1682d5a59e673ecfbcdd34155713180df84"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1608746153,"nonce":"oKX3Lt/KcLswrWZm2os8zs0YUuo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3NzM5NjEyOTI=","github-url":"https://github.com/OPEN-NEXT/OKH-LOSH/issues/54","origin":"github"},"title":"Catch-All properties","message":"The two properties\n\n```\nokh:functionalMetadata\nokh:productionMetadata\n```\n\nare kind of catch all things.\nTo me it is unclear how they should be used, and how one could make use of this data.\nAs I read their description, they want to store multiple structured values into a single unstructured field, for example:\n\n```\nomg:myFunnyMachine\n  a okh:MOSH ;\n  okh:functionalMetadata '''\n  length: 70cm\n  weight: 50kg\n  ''' ;\n  .\n```\n\nI think this is not what we want, as everyone could put different data in a different format in this field (someone else might put JSON data there, for example), and we already have a structured data format right there: RDF\n\nI would think, we rather not have this data at all, then in this way.\nAlternatively, this data could be there as separate fields, not from our standard, which - if widely adopted in the community - could be integrated into our standard. Until ten, it might look like this:\n\n```\nomg:myFunnyMachine\n  a okh:MOSH ;\n  schema:width '70cm' ;\n  schema:weight '50kg' ;\n  .\n```","files":null}]}